fields.description:
On a fresh 3.4.0 installation I'm getting log messages that dns properties cannot be found. It does not appear to be a problem, but opening a ticket to track. I don't see the same message for any other properties that are registered.

Procedure to reproduce:

1. Install 3.4.0 cloud controller
2. Run "euca_conf --initialize"
3. Start the eucalyptus-cloud service
4. Error message appears while cloud is bootstrapping

{code}
2013-10-10 13:05:23  WARN 000000509 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.services.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.component.TopologyDnsResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.services.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:23  WARN 000000513 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.split_horizon.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.vm.dns.SplitHorizonResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.split_horizon.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:23  INFO 000000761 DBCleanupService         | Calling cloudwatch db cleanup service
2013-10-10 13:05:23  WARN 000000522 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.recursive.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.dns.resolvers.RecursiveDnsResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.recursive.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:23  WARN 000000511 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.util.dns.DnsResolvers.enabled value=null propName=dns.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:23  WARN 000000510 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.ns.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.util.dns.NameserverResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.ns.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:24  WARN 000000663 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.services.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.component.TopologyDnsResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.services.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 13:05:25  WARN 000000663 StaticPropertyEntry      | Failed to get property: dns.split_horizon.enabled because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.vm.dns.SplitHorizonResolver.enabled value=null propName=dns.split_horizon.enabled id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]

comments.body:
This issue also can show up with properties that are not dns. prefixed, for example:

(I added a stack trace to the log)
2013-10-10 15:43:05  WARN | Failed to get property: bootstrap.webservices.client_internal_timeout_secs because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.ws.StackConfiguration.client_internal_timeout_secs value=null propName=bootstrap.webservices.client_internal_timeout_secs id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 15:43:05  WARN | Failed to get property: bootstrap.webservices.client_idle_timeout_secs because of example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.ws.StackConfiguration.client_idle_timeout_secs value=null propName=bootstrap.webservices.client_idle_timeout_secs id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
2013-10-10 15:43:05  WARN | java.util.NoSuchElementException: example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.ws.StackConfiguration.client_internal_timeout_secs value=null propName=bootstrap.webservices.client_internal_timeout_secs id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
java.util.NoSuchElementException: example: [StaticDatabasePropertyEntry fieldName=com.eucalyptus.ws.StackConfiguration.client_internal_timeout_secs value=null propName=bootstrap.webservices.client_internal_timeout_secs id=null version=null creationTimestamp=null lastUpdateTimestamp=null naturalId=null]
        at com.eucalyptus.entities.Entities.maybeDefinitelyExample(Entities.java:487)
        at com.eucalyptus.entities.Entities.uniqueResult(Entities.java:451)
        at com.eucalyptus.configurable.StaticDatabasePropertyEntry.lookup(StaticDatabasePropertyEntry.java:137)
        at com.eucalyptus.configurable.StaticPropertyEntry.getValue(StaticPropertyEntry.java:103)
        at com.eucalyptus.ws.DeferredPropertiesBootstrapper$1.run(DeferredPropertiesBootstrapper.java:126)
        at java.util.concurrent.Executors$RunnableAdapter.call(Executors.java:471)
        at java.util.concurrent.FutureTask$Sync.innerRun(FutureTask.java:334)
        at java.util.concurrent.FutureTask.run(FutureTask.java:166)
        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor.runWorker(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:1145)
        at java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker.run(ThreadPoolExecutor.java:615)
        at java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:724)


This appears to occur when a query is made against a db query that has not yet been entered.  The default value is used, and the db value is (eventually) put in.  Once start up, these values can be read and modified, and do appear to be in the db.  This may be a timing issue, does not appear 3.4 critical.
errors in the logs are not functionality impacting to the end user.  The dns variables will be set after bootstrap of the components.
